  <p class="intro">This page says what elliodelics does in simple language. The <a href="/">full page</a> says the same things with more style.</p>

  <h2>What we do</h2>
  <p>elliodelics builds software. We work with companies in the psychedelic field. That includes clinics, retreats, research groups, and companies developing new medicines.</p>
  <p>Here is the main idea. One day a big deal, an investor, or an insurer will ask hard questions about how you handle people's data. We make sure the right answers exist before they ask.</p>
  <p>We do five kinds of work.</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Getting you ready for hard questions.</strong> We check how you handle data, fix the gaps, and write the answers down.</li>
    <li><strong>Protecting data.</strong> We keep people's information safe. We follow laws like GDPR.</li>
    <li><strong>Checking your AI tools.</strong> Many AI tools touch private data. We find them, read their rules, and limit what they can reach.</li>
    <li><strong>Building products.</strong> Websites, apps, research tools, and the systems behind them.</li>
    <li><strong>Leadership.</strong> Mike can act as your part-time head of engineering.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Who runs it</h2>
  <p>Mike Elliott runs elliodelics. He has built software for fifteen years. He led engineering teams at two large companies. He also studies psychedelics and consciousness at a university.</p>
  <p>It is a small studio on purpose. Mike does the work himself. He brings in trusted helpers when a project needs them.</p>

  <h2>Why it matters</h2>
  <p>Software in this field holds sensitive information. A leak could hurt real people. So we build privacy in from the first day, not at the end.</p>
  <p>We answered the hard questions for ourselves first. You can read <a href="/answers">our own answers</a>.</p>

  <h2>How to reach us</h2>
  <p>Email <a href="mailto:mike@elliodelics.com">mike@elliodelics.com</a>. Say what you are building and what you need. Your message goes straight to Mike. He usually replies within a few days. The first call is free.</p>
